This project is an OCaml translation of the Rust terminal Mermaid renderer
`mermaid.rs` from the xai-org/grok-build repository:

  https://github.com/xai-org/grok-build/blob/b189869b7755d2b482969acf6c92da3ecfeffd36/crates/codegen/xai-grok-markdown/src/mermaid.rs

The original is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE).
The OCaml port re-implements its behavior in a new language; the diagram
parsing, layout, and box-drawing logic derive from that original work.

Modifications from the original include (non-exhaustive):
  - Translation from Rust to OCaml.
  - Removal of the ratatui dependency: styled output is exposed as a
    TUI-agnostic (class-tagged span) model instead of ratatui Line/Span/Style.
  - Adaptation of Unicode width handling to uucp/uutf.
  - Repackaging as an opam library with its own test suites.
